MOVIES by Alex Ungerman 7:29 PM PDT, May 04, 2016
Playing EXCLUSIVE: Russell Crowe, Amanda Seyfried and Aaron Paul Get Emotional in New Film 'Fathers and Daughters' – Watch the Trailer
Russell Crowe and Amanda Seyfried are exploring the hardships of family life in their newest movie.
Just in time for Mother's Day and Father's Day, Fathers and Daughters explores the life of a widowed father (Crowe) who struggles to reconnect with his adult daughter (Seyfried) after suffering a mental breakdown.
The movie, which also stars Aaron Paul, Diane Kruger, Quvenzhané Wallis, Octavia Spencer, and Jane Fonda, is in theaters from Vertical Entertainment on July 8, following an exclusive DIRECTV release on May 5.